White House Press Secretary Sean Spicer has resigned from his position. President Donald Trump has accepted his resignation and expressed gratitude for Spicer's work on behalf of the administration and the American people. Spicer will continue to serve until August. In his statement, Spicer thanked President Trump and his staff for their work in advancing the interests of the American people. He expressed confidence that President Trump's commitment to making America great again will lead to continued success in the future.